{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I wanted to show them that I wasn't scared to come even into this lair of theirs.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were simply powerless, afraid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't blame them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The class of about 30, 32, whatever it was had at least 12, 14 Hitler Youth members there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that teacher would have gotten into an awful lot of trouble if any of them would have taken it into their minds to cause it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there-- there were many incidents of people who denounced and were then hauled off to jail and beaten up or worse.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were-- there were murders happening right after the Nazis came to power.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember the story that two, three Jewish attorneys who had defended communists, for instance, were hunted down in the streets and-- and lynched right then and there, murdered right then and there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we knew there was danger.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But then it was so unprecedented that the only thing I can say looking back is that we always felt that we could live with it, that we would outlive this what shall we call it fever of illness that had seized a part of Germany, as we thought at the time.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the Nazis, of course, were also very cunning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They understood this totally and they did it bit by bit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, it was the salami tactic, slice by slice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And after you'd gotten used to one, them came the next restriction and then after that, an additional one and this lawsuit and this denial.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was done so cunningly, so cleverly-- psychologically, really, you might say masterly-- that we felt, well, first of all, you could try to live with it.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
